article.description: — Isaiah Rivera's 24 points helped UIC defeat Valparaiso 70-64 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Rivera scores 24 in UIC's 70-64 victory against Valparaiso
article.linkText: Rivera scores 24 in UIC's 70-64 victory against Valparaiso
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Isaiah Rivera's 24 points helped UIC defeat Valparaiso 70-64 on Saturday night. Rivera also had five rebounds for the Flames (8-7, 1/3 Missouri Valley Conference). Filip scored 13 points and added six rebounds. Marquise Kennedy had eight points and finished 4 of 4 from the floor. Isaiah Stafford finished with 19 points for the Beacons (4-11, 0-4). Darius DeAveiro added 11 points and four assists for Valparaiso. Jaxon Edwards also had 10 points, 11 rebounds and three blocks. The loss is the ninth straight for the Beacons. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
